raylib
------------------------------------------
raylib is highly inspired by Borland BGI graphics lib and by XNA framework and
it's specially well suited for prototyping, tooling, graphical applications,
embedded systems and education.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.6-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libglfw-devel-3.3.8-1bl1
  libglfw3-3.3.8-1bl1
  libraylib-devel-4.2.0-1bl1
  libraylib420-4.2.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.40-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.36.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libglfw-devel-3.3.8-1bl1
  lua-5.3.6-4
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/raysan5/raylib

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/raysan5/raylib/archive/refs/tags/4.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack raylib-4.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./raylib-4.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/raylib-4.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/raylib-4.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraylib420-4.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraylib-devel-4.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(raylib)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/raylib.README
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/BINDINGS.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/CHANGELOG
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/CONVENTIONS.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/FAQ.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/HISTORY.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/ROADMAP.md

(libraylib420)
  /usr/bin/cygraylib-420.dll

(libraylib-devel)
  /usr/include/raylib.h
  /usr/include/raymath.h
  /usr/include/rlgl.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/raylib/raylib-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/raylib/raylib-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/libraylib.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/raylib.pc

